<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D47FFA0FF4DFD46FDB5FD5B" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="207B96733D47FFA0FF4DFD46FDB5FD5B" blockId="52.[151,1437,582,1437]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D47FFA0FF4DFD46FEA3FD3F" bold="true" box="[199,328,655,681]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Etymology</emphasis>
. The epithet in apposition referring to the mythological vampire Dracula, alluding to the large chelicerae, which resemble Dracula’s fangs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D47FFA0FF4DFD1FFA73FC83" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D47FFA0FF4DFD1FFA73FC83" blockId="52.[151,1437,582,1437]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D47FFA0FF4DFD1FFEA9FD66" bold="true" box="[199,322,726,752]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D47FFA0FE33FD1EFD84FD67" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[441,623,727,753]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracula" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D47FFA0FE33FD1EFD84FD67" box="[441,623,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Patrera dracula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D47FFA0FDF2FD1EFD52FD67" bold="true" box="[632,697,727,753]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D47FFA0FDF2FD1EFD52FD67" box="[632,697,727,753]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from those of the remaining species of the genus by the bifid, long retrolateral tibial apophysis and by the proximally inserted, arched embolus (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D47FFA0FA8FFD32FABEFC83" box="[1285,1365,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[217,1368,181,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@51.[217,1370,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 27A–F. Patrera dracula n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9556): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cdp, cheliceral dorsal projection; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468443/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
D–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D47FFA0FF4DFCD7FE49FAA7" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="207B96733D47FFA0FF4DFCD7FAD7FA9B" blockId="52.[151,1437,582,1437]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D47FFA0FF4DFCD7FEB2FCAE" bold="true" box="[199,345,798,824]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D47FFA0FED5FCD6FE72FCAF" box="[351,409,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D47FFA0FE2DFCD6FDFFFCAF" box="[423,532,799,825]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-9556). Carapace brown with dark patches, darker in the cephalic region (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D47FFA0FF2AFC8AFEE1FCCB" box="[160,266,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[217,1368,181,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@51.[217,1370,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 27A–F. Patrera dracula n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9556): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cdp, cheliceral dorsal projection; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468443/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 27A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae brown. Labium and endites brown. Sternum yellow. Legs yellow, darkest at metatarsi and tarsi. Abdomen uniformly gray. Spinnerets gray (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D47FFA0FD41FCAEFCDCFC17" box="[715,823,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[217,1368,181,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@51.[217,1370,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 27A–F. Patrera dracula n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9556): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cdp, cheliceral dorsal projection; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468443/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 27A</figureCitation>
). Total length 4.69, carapace length 1.72, width 1.62, high 0.96. Clypeus height 0.08. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.07, ALE 0.16, PME 0.16, PLE 0.15; AME–AME 0.19, AME–ALE 0.28, PME–PME 0.39, PME–PLE 0.38, ALE–PLE 0.34. Chelicerae 1.57 long, four promarginal teeth, five retromarginal teeth; large; cheliceral ventral projection large and cheliceral dorsal projection sharp (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D47FFA0FF68FC3EFED9FB87" box="[226,306,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[217,1368,181,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@51.[217,1370,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 27A–F. Patrera dracula n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9556): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, dorsal view; C chelicerae, ventral view; D left palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view; F palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Cdp, cheliceral dorsal projection; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–F: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468443/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
B–C). Leg measurements: leg I—femur 3.93/ patella 1.05/ tibia 4.7/ metatarsus 3.98/ tarsus 1.84/ total 15.50; II—3.23/ 0.98/ 3.69/ 3.21/ 1.37/ 12.48; III—2.39/ 0.74/ 2.01/ 2.46/ 0.85/ 8.45; IV—3.32/ 0.81/ 2.76/ 3.74/ 1.05/ 11.68. Leg spination: I—tibia v2-2-0; II—tibia v2-2-0, metatarsus v2-2-0; III—tibia d1-0-1, p0-1-1, r0-1-1, metatarsus d0-1-0, v2-2-0, p1-1-2, r1-1-2; IV—tibia d1-0-1, p0-1-1, r0-1-1, metatarsus v2-2-1, p1-2-2, r0-1-1. Abdomen: length 2.74. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis bifid with the ventral branch wider, shorter than dorsal branch, which is thin; cymbium twice as long as tibia length; subtegulum longer than wide; tegulum longer than wide, with a very small ventral tegular process; median apophysis short, curved, laminar and medially situated; embolus short, laminar, curved, apically filiform, with narrow base and proximally inserted on the tegulum (
